<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare,Products.Contributor">
    <body>A bookmark is a marker, or flag, that lets you create hyperlinks to specific locations within topics<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> or documents</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> (rather than to another topic file in general)</MadCap:conditionalText>. You can insert a bookmark at a specific location in your topic<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> or document</MadCap:conditionalText> (e.g., at a subheading) and then insert a hyperlink that "connects" to that bookmark. This is a useful feature, for example, if you have a somewhat lengthy topic<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> or document</MadCap:conditionalText> and want the user to be able to locate a specific place in the topic<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> or document</MadCap:conditionalText> quickly.</body>
</html>